---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../../components/shared/Container.astro';
import MonoEyebrow from '../../components/shared/MonoEyebrow.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Blue Business"
  description="Privacy Policy of Blue Innovation B.V. (Blue Business). No tracking cookies, no analytics tools. The data we do process, why and for how long."
  canonicalPath="/en/privacy/"
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', path: '/en/' }, { name: 'Privacy Policy', path: '/en/privacy/' }]}
>
  <section class="pt-[140px] md:pt-[180px] pb-10">
    <Container size="narrow">
      <MonoEyebrow text="// Legal" tone="accent-hi" class="mb-5 block" />
      <h1 class="text-h1 font-medium" style="letter-spacing: var(--tracking-tight); line-height: 1.02;">
        <span class="block text-fg">Privacy</span>
        <span class="block text-accent">Policy.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-body text-fg-dim mt-6 max-w-[60ch]">
        Blue Innovation B.V., version April 2026. Registered with the Dutch Chamber of Commerce under number 80387578, with registered office at Rietsingel 46, 2136 LB Zwaanshoek, the Netherlands.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 p-4 rounded-[10px] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/[0.06] border border-[var(--color-accent-line)] max-w-[60ch]">
        <p class="text-[14px] text-fg-dim">
          This English version is provided for convenience. The legally binding version is the Dutch <a href="/nl/privacy/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">Privacy Policy</a>. In case of any discrepancy, the Dutch version prevails.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-24">
    <Container size="narrow">
      <div class="prose-legal space-y-6 text-[15px] text-fg-dim" style="line-height: 1.7;">
        <p>
          This website (<a href="https://bluebusiness.nl" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">bluebusiness.nl</a>) is intentionally minimal when it comes to data. No analytics tools that follow you around, no advertising cookies, no social-media trackers, no cookie banner — because there's nothing to ask consent for. Below we explain exactly what data we do process, why, for how long, and who has access.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Data controller</h2>
        <p>
          Blue Innovation B.V. (trading as Blue Business), Rietsingel 46, 2136 LB Zwaanshoek, the Netherlands, KvK 80387578. Email: <a href="mailto:info@bluebusiness.nl" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">info@bluebusiness.nl</a>. For privacy questions you can use the same address.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">What data do we process?</h2>
        <p>
          Only data that you actively provide. Specifically:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong class="text-fg font-medium">Contact form</strong> — if you fill in the form on <a href="/en/contact/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">/contact/</a>: your name, email address, optionally your company name, project type, project scale and your description of the project. Purpose: to get in touch and answer your question. Legal basis: your request (pre-contractual measures, art. 6(1)(b) GDPR).</li>
          <li><strong class="text-fg font-medium">Email correspondence</strong> — if you email <a href="mailto:info@bluebusiness.nl" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">info@bluebusiness.nl</a> directly: your email address, possibly your name and signature, and the contents of the message. Purpose: to answer your question. Legal basis: your request.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">How long do we keep it?</h2>
        <p>
          Contact form submissions and email correspondence are retained for up to two (2) years after the last contact, unless an engagement results from it — in which case they fall under the retention period of the related administration (seven years on a tax basis).
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Processors and third parties</h2>
        <p>
          To run the site we use three external services. All three have a data processing agreement (DPA) with us, or offer one as standard:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong class="text-fg font-medium">Vercel Inc. (USA)</strong> — hosting and CDN. With every page request Vercel processes your IP address, user agent and path for caching, security (DDoS) and debugging. Vercel does not store identifiers to track you back. We use Vercel Web Analytics — cookieless, hashed-and-anonymised IP, no data shared with third parties. <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">Vercel privacy policy</a>.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-fg font-medium">Formspree Inc. (USA)</strong> — contact form processing. When you submit the form, the filled-in fields go via Formspree to our inbox. Formspree temporarily stores the submission for forwarding and spam filtering. <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">Formspree privacy policy</a>.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-fg font-medium">Google Fonts (Google LLC, USA)</strong> — typography (Geist and Geist Mono) is served from Google's font CDN. When loading a page, Google processes your IP address and user agent. No cookies. We're investigating self-hosting to remove this dependency in a future update.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Both US parties operate under the EU-US Data Privacy Framework. For onward transfers, Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) apply.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">No analytics, no advertising cookies, no social trackers</h2>
        <p>
          This website uses <strong class="text-fg font-medium">no</strong> Google Analytics, no Hotjar, no Meta Pixel, no LinkedIn Insights, no Facebook/Instagram/X/YouTube cookies, no retargeting, and no profiling. The only cookies your browser may store are strictly functional (e.g. local CSS preferences) and contain no personal data. That's why you see no cookie banner — there's no consent to ask for data we don't collect.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Security</h2>
        <p>
          Traffic to the site goes over HTTPS. Contact form submissions travel encrypted to Formspree and from there encrypted to our inbox (TLS). Emails are kept inside our email environment with multi-factor authentication.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Under the GDPR you have the right to access, correction, deletion, restriction of processing, data portability and objection. Send an email to <a href="mailto:info@bluebusiness.nl" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">info@bluebusiness.nl</a> with your request; we'll respond within 30 days. For verification we may ask for additional information. Have a complaint about how we handle your data? You can contact the <a href="https://www.autoriteitpersoonsgegevens.nl/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">Dutch Data Protection Authority</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy when our tools, processes or the law change. The date at the top always reflects the most recent version.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-h3 font-medium text-fg mt-10 mb-3">Apps we build</h2>
        <p>
          This policy only covers the website <a href="https://bluebusiness.nl" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hi underline underline-offset-2">bluebusiness.nl</a>. The apps we've built for clients and as our own products (Visit Bonaire, Bonaire Cruisers, Medewerker, GAST, Run2Forty2) have their own privacy statements — find them in the App Store and Play Store of each app, and on the publisher's website.
        </p>

        <p class="text-body text-fg-faint mt-16 pt-6 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
          Last updated: April 2026.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
